    "created_at": "2013-03-13T23:38:28Z",
    "updated_at": "2013-03-13T23:38:28Z",
    "body": "A `mutate_values` method is added in #5365, and I think that covers 99% of the functionality that would be possible by mutating while iterating. It's possible to allow removing entries while iterating... but it would require `unsafe` blocks to actually implement it for most of the containers.\n\nClosing this anyway because there's no way to actually mutate it while using normal iteration or lazy iterators since they both freeze it.\n",
